
#######################################
Penetration Testing Execution Standards
#######################################

Seven Categories of PTES w.r.t toolkits

1- Pre-Engagement Interactions
2- Intelligence Gathering
3- Threat Modeling
4- Vulnerability Analysis
5- Exploitation
6- Post-Exploitation
7- Reporting

#############################
Types of Penetration Testing
############################

Overt Penetration Testing
  White Box

Covert Penetration Testing
  Black Box

#######
Toolkit
#######

Intelligence Gathering & Fingerprinting
---------------------------------------
  Web Application Firewalls
    wafw00f

Enumeration & Reconnaissance
-----------------------------
  WordLists
    Seclists
  Domain Name Server (DNS)
    Domain Enumeration
      Massdns
      Dnsenum
    Subdomain Enumeration (with wordlists)
    	Knockpy
    	Sublist3r
  Extracting Data
    Scrapy
  Encoding & Decoding
  	CyberChef

Scanning/Fuzzers/Discovery
----------------------------
  Web Applications
    Scanning/Fuzzers
	    Wfuzz
      Sn1per
    Brute-Force Directories / Directory Traverse
      Dirb
      Dirbuster
      Gobuster
  Network
    nmap/zenmap
    masscan
    unicornscan
    netdiscover
  Content Management Systems (CMS)
  	Whatcms.org
  	Wpscan
  	Joomscan
  	CMSmap

Exploitation
------------
  Web Applications
    Burp Suite
      Chrome Extensions/Add-on's
        FoxyProxy
        CookieEditor/CookieEditor+
        BuiltWith/Wappalyzer
    Cross Site Scipting (XSS)
    	XSStrike
    Database
      Server Query Language (SQL)
        Sqlmap

Unsorted
--------
OWASP Zed Attack Proxy (ZAP)
